parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the liftgate and sliding door can cause injuries, accidents, or damage to the vehicle, as the doors may fall off or slam shut unexpectedly.
symptoms: The liftgate or sliding door falls off or comes off the track
the door slams shut without warning
the door is difficult to open or close
the door is not securely attached to the vehicle
the door falls off when opening or closing
the door is stuck or jammed.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the axle and transmission mounts can cause loss of control, accidents, or damage to the vehicle, as the axle may explode or the transmission mounts may bend.
symptoms: Noise or vibrations from under the vehicle
the vehicle is difficult to control or stops suddenly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The peeling of paint and body damage can cause distractions to other drivers, potentially leading to accidents, and may also reduce the vehicle's value.
The failure of the rear hatch/liftgate latch can cause the door to open while driving, resulting in loss of cargo, accidents, or injuries to passengers.
symptoms: The rear hatch/liftgate latch fails to hold the door open
the door comes open while driving
the door is difficult to open or close
the latch warning light comes on
the latch has a delayed or failed engagement
the bolts or screws fall out of the latch assembly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission failure can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to move, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the transmission fails to engage or disengage
the transmission fails to shift gears properly
the transmission jumps out of gear.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission slippage can cause the vehicle to lose power, stall, or become unable to move, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: the transmission fails to engage or disengage

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Transmission leaks can cause the transmission to fail, leading to a loss of power, stalling, or the vehicle becoming unable to move, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
